headline: S&P 500, Nasdaq Try to Secure a Winning Week
summary: After starting the day on a more somber note, the S&P 500 is up 0.1%, while the Nasdaq is up 0.5%.  Goldman Sachs, Home Depot, and Sherwin-Williams were among Friday's Dow decliners.  "As a long-awaited rate cut approaches, stocks continue to press to new highs," wrote Daniel Skelly, Head of Morgan Stanley's Wealth Management Market Research & Strategy Team.
